433.Question: Give me 10 nature reserves that are west of townlands.
433.Query: SELECT distinct ?nr WHERE { ?nr rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_nature_reserve. ?nr geo:hasGeometry ?nrGeo. ?nrGeo geo:asWKT ?nrWKt. ?townland rdf:type y2geoo:OSI_Townland. ?townland geo:hasGeometry ?TownlandGeo. ?TownlandGeo geo:asWKT ?TownlandWKt. FILTER (strdf:left(?nrWKt, ?TownlandWKt)) } LIMIT 10

434.Question: Which lakes border villages?
434.Query: SELECT ?lake WHERE { ?village a y2geoo:OSM_village . ?village geo:hasGeometry ?villageGeom . ?villageGeom geo:asWKT ?xWKT . ?lake a y2geoo:OSM_stream . ?lake geo:hasGeometry ?lakeGeom . ?lakeGeom geo:asWKT ?yWKT . FILTER(geof:sfTouches(?xWKT,?yWKT)). }

435.Question: Which streams flow through cities?
435.Query: select distinct ?x where { ?x rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_stream; geo:hasGeometry ?cGeom1. ?cGeom1 geo:asWKT ?cWKT1. ?y rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_city; geo:hasGeometry ?cGeom2. ?cGeom2 geo:asWKT ?cWKT2.  FILTER(geof:sfCrosses(?cWKT1,?cWKT2)) }

436.Question: Which forests are entirely within a Barony and intersect with townlands?
436.Query: SELECT DISTINCT ?l WHERE { ?m a y2geoo:OSI_Barony.    ?m geo:hasGeometry ?mg .    ?mg geo:asWKT ?mw .     ?l a y2geoo:OSM_forest.    ?l geo:hasGeometry ?lg .    ?lg geo:asWKT ?lw . ?lake a y2geoo:OSI_Townland.    ?lake geo:hasGeometry ?lg1 .    ?lg1 geo:asWKT ?lw1 .    FILTER(geof:sfWithin(?lw,?mw)). FILTER(strdf:intersects(?lw, ?lw1)). }

437.Question: Identify any nature reserves that are situated south of a forested area.
437.Query: SELECT DISTINCT ?nature_reserve WHERE {   ?nature_reserve rdf:type <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_nature_reserve> .   ?nature_reserve geo:hasGeometry ?nature_reserve_geo .   ?nature_reserve_geo geo:asWKT ?nature_reserve_geoWKT .  ?forest rdf:type <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_forest> .   ?forest geo:hasGeometry ?forest_geo .   ?forest_geo geo:asWKT ?forest_geoWKT .  FILTER(strdf:below(?nature_reserve_geoWKT, ?forest_geoWKT)  ) }

438.Question: Which towns have beaches?
438.Query: SELECT DISTINCT ?city WHERE { ?city rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_town . ?city geo:hasGeometry ?geoC . ?geoC geo:asWKT ?cWKT . ?beach rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_beach . ?beach geo:hasGeometry ?geoB . ?geoB geo:asWKT ?bWKT . FILTER(geof:sfWithin(?bWKT, ?cWKT)) }

439.Question: Which rural areas intersect with lakes?
439.Query: select DISTINCT ?x where { ?x rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_lake . ?x geo:hasGeometry ?xGeom. ?xGeom geo:asWKT ?xWKT. ?o rdf:type y2geoo:OSI_Rural_Area . ?o geo:hasGeometry ?oGeom. ?oGeom geo:asWKT ?iWKT. FILTER(geof:sfIntersects(?xWKT,?iWKT )) }

440.Question: What urban centers possess beaches?
440.Query: SELECT DISTINCT ?city WHERE { ?city rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_city . ?city geo:hasGeometry ?geoC . ?geoC geo:asWKT ?cWKT . ?beach rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_beach . ?beach geo:hasGeometry ?geoB . ?geoB geo:asWKT ?bWKT . FILTER(geof:sfWithin(?bWKT, ?cWKT)) }

441.Question: Which lakes are linked to a woodland area?
441.Query: select DISTINCT ?x where { ?x rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_lake . ?x geo:hasGeometry ?xGeom. ?xGeom geo:asWKT ?xWKT. ?o rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_forest . ?o geo:hasGeometry ?oGeom. ?oGeom geo:asWKT ?iWKT. FILTER(geof:sfIntersects(?xWKT,?iWKT )) }

442.Question: Which States of the US border with at most 2 other States?
442.Query: SELECT DISTINCT ?state { yago:United_States geo:hasGeometry ?usGeo . ?usGeo geo:asWKT ?usWKT . ?state rdf:type y2geoo:GADM_2ndOrder_AdministrativeUnit . ?state geo:hasGeometry ?sGeo . ?sGeo geo:asWKT ?sWKT . ?state2 rdf:type y2geoo:GADM_2ndOrder_AdministrativeUnit . ?state2 geo:hasGeometry ?s2Geo . ?s2Geo geo:asWKT ?s2WKT . FILTER(?state != ?state2 && geof:sfWithin(?sWKT,?usWKT) && geof:sfWithin(?s2WKT,?usWKT) && geof:sfTouches(?sWKT,?s2WKT)) . } GROUP BY ?state HAVING(COUNT(?state2)<=2)

443.Question: Is there a lake that touches both a forest and a village?
443.Query: ASK { ?lake rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_lake . ?lake geo:hasGeometry ?lGeo . ?lGeo geo:asWKT ?lWKT . ?village rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_village . ?village geo:hasGeometry ?vGeo . ?vGeo geo:asWKT ?vWKT . ?forest rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_forest . ?forest geo:hasGeometry ?fGeo . ?fGeo geo:asWKT ?fWKT . FILTER(geof:sfTouches(?vWKT,?lWKT) && geof:sfTouches(?fWKT,?lWKT)) . }

444.Question: Give me a stream that crosses at least two lakes.
444.Query: SELECT ?stream WHERE { ?stream rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_stream . ?stream geo:hasGeometry ?sGeo . ?sGeo geo:asWKT ?sWKT . ?lake rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_lake . ?lake geo:hasGeometry ?lGeo . ?lGeo geo:asWKT ?lWKT . FILTER(geof:sfCrosses(?sWKT,?lWKT)) . } GROUP BY ?stream HAVING(COUNT(?lake)>=3) LIMIT 1

445.Question: Which localities are adjacent to lakes?
445.Query: SELECT DISTINCT ?locality where{   ?locality a y2geoo:OSM_locality.   ?locality geo:hasGeometry ?localityGeometry .   ?localityGeometry geo:asWKT ?localityWKT .    ?p a y2geoo:OSM_lake.   ?p geo:hasGeometry ?pGeometry .   ?pGeometry geo:asWKT ?pWKT .      FILTER(geof:sfTouches(?localityWKT,?pWKT)). }

446.Question: Give me 5 streams that are on islands?
446.Query: SELECT DISTINCT ?river WHERE {       ?island a y2geoo:OSM_island .   ?island geo:hasGeometry ?islandGeom .   ?islandGeom geo:asWKT ?xWKT .       ?river a y2geoo:OSM_stream .   ?river geo:hasGeometry ?riverGeom .   ?riverGeom geo:asWKT ?yWKT .       FILTER(geof:sfWithin(?yWKT,?xWKT)) } LIMIT 5

447.Question: Which islands are situated within the boundaries of lakes?
447.Query: SELECT ?village WHERE { ?village a y2geoo:OSM_island .   ?village geo:hasGeometry ?villageGeom .   ?villageGeom geo:asWKT ?xWKT .       ?lake a y2geoo:OSM_lake .   ?lake geo:hasGeometry ?lakeGeom .   ?lakeGeom geo:asWKT ?yWKT .       FILTER( geof:sfContains(?yWKT,?xWKT)) }
